<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title>ColorSnapper</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/s/screen.css" type="text/css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="b-header">
      <div class="b-header-wrap">
        <div class="b-logo-container">
          <a href="/i/logo-full.png"><img src="/i/logo-sm.png" width="256" height="256" alt="ColorSnapper Icon" class="jLoupe"></a>
          
          <div class="b-appstore">
            <a href="http://example.com/">Available in the Mac App Store</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="b-logo-text">
          <h1 class="b-logo">ColorSnapper</h1>
          <h2 class="b-tagline">Pixel perfect color picker for designers and developers</h2>
          <p>ColorSnapper allows you to <em>preview your design</em> with <em>pixel perfect</em> precision as well as to <em>copy into clipboard</em> the color code in popular developer’s formats such as <em>HEX, CSS3, NSColor</em> etc.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>
    

    <section class="b-usage">
      <div class="b-usage-wrap">
        <ol>
          <li class="b-usage__item">
            <h2>Point &amp; Shoot</h2>
            <img src="/i/b-usage-1.png" width="189" height="189" alt="Point &amp; Shoot">
          </li>
          <li class="b-usage__item">
            <h2>Paste &amp; Use</h2>
            <img src="/i/b-usage-2.png" width="237" height="189" alt="Paste &amp; Use">
          </li>
          <li class="b-usage__item">
            <h2>Select &amp; Reuse</h2>
            <img src="/i/b-usage-3.png" width="224" height="256" alt="Select &amp; Reuse">
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="b-features">
      <div class="b-features-wrap">
        <div class="b-features__item">
          <h2>Under your fingertips</h2>
          <p>ColorSnapper is always under your fingertips. You define which shortcut to use globally. No matter what application are you using now, just press the shortcut and it’s here!</p>
        </div>
      
        <div class="b-features__item">
          <h2>Any format you want</h2>
          <p>ColorSnapper formats the picked color in lots of handy formats no matter what are you working on: web-site, OS X or iOS application. And there is alternative format which is accesible by pressing down Alt key.</p>
        </div>
      
        <div class="b-features__item">
          <h2>Pixel perfect</h2>
          <p>With ColorSnapper you have can pick any color off your screen. With magnification from 2x till 10x you can see every aspect of your design.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="b-footer">
      <div class="b-footer-wrap">
        <p>&copy; Koole Sache, 2011</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
    
    <script type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8" src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.5.0/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8" src="/js/jquery.jloupe.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>